In one of my previous posts, I discussed configuring multibranch pipeline seed jobs using Jenkins configuration as code plugin
Below is an example of configuring a declarative pipeline job from a bitbucket repo, running at midnight every day
- script: &gt; pipelineJob(&#39;sample-job&#39;) { definition { cpsScm { scriptPath &#39;job1/Jenkinsfile&#39; ## If the Jenkins job is in a nested folder scm { git { remote { url &#39;https://github.com/Vikaspogu/sample-repo&#39; credentials &#39;sample-creds&#39; } branch &#39;*/master&#39; extensions {} } } triggers { cron(&#39;@midnight&#39;) } } } }
